    <Terminal canbeselected="false" msg="ItemMsgInteractSelect" AllowInGameEditing="false" drawhudwhenequipped="true" welcomemessage="The Abridged Necronomicon\n\nHubismal and Sons Publishing\n\nCopyright 2036\n\nType 'intro' into the topmost box and then press enter to begin.">
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nWELCOME\n---\nWelcome to the Abridged Necronomicon!\n\nThis book is for cultists who don't have time to read the long, boring necronomicon, and teaches you the basics of occultism like how to summon scary stuff, talk to the dead, and the basics of blood rituals!\n\nThis electronic book is navigated by entering terms into the topmost box. Enter the term 'index' to view a list of available terms.">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq intro" />
      </StatusEffect>
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nINDEX\n---\nHere is an index of available terms followed by what their pages are:\nglassaltar: directions for using the blood altar to get items\npentagram: basic usage of the summoning pentagram\ncoldcavern: ritual directions for summoning the 'Cold Cavern Sampler'\nglow: ritual directions for summoning the 'Glowpocalypse'\n: ritual directions for summoning the 'Calyx Outbreak'\n">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq index" />
      </StatusEffect>
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nGLASS ALTAR + GUTTER DAGGER\n---\nCongratulations on your purchase of a honkcraftian altar and dagger combo! These items serve to aid to collect blood and summon items.\n\nYour GUTTER DAGGER has a bar on it that indicates how much blood it has collected. Stab things to gain blood! You may be tempted to stab your COLLEAGUES, but remember that EUROPAN CREATURES provide more blood overall. Only draw blood from human subjects with their CONSENT.\n\nYour GLASS ALTAR is where blood can be redeemed for SPECIAL ITEMS via blood ritual. Place your GUTTER DAGGER inside of the altar, and equip the altar in your hand to see the options. You must have the indicated amount of blood in the dagger or the ritual will not work! Wait for the ritual to finish, and your item will appear inside of the altar, allowing removal.">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq glassaltar" />
      </StatusEffect>
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nSUMMONING PENTAGRAM\n---\nIf you want to bring forsaken life into the world, look no further than your SUMMONING PENTAGRAM.\n\nYou can create a summoning pentagram with your GLASS ALTAR provided you have enough blood (refer to section 'glassaltar'). Equip it, aim with the right mouse button, and place with your USE key (E or left mouse). Once your pentagram is laid out, it cannot be removed nondestructively!\n\nYou can now SUMMON CREATURES. Various SUMMONING ITEMS in the game can be placed in your pentagram and initiate a ritual, and will also spawn some LOOT, provided you don't mind a little bit of fighting! Refer to these sections to learn about a few basic summons!\ncoldcavern: ritual directions for summoning the 'Cold Cavern Sampler'\nglow: ritual directions for summoning the `Glowpocalypse'\nhusk: ritual directions for summoning the 'Calyx Outbreak'\n...and many more! Experiment with items closely associated with living creatures (eg husk stingers for husks, paralyzant for thalamus, etc).">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq pentagram" />
      </StatusEffect>
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nRITUAL: COLD CAVERN SAMPLER\n---\nSummoning Item: Mudraptor Shell\nSummons Per Item: 2\nTime Required: 45 seconds\nSuccessful Outcome: 3 Hydrophixate, 1 Stantium, 2 Crawlers\nChance of Failure: 5%\nFailure Outcome: Pentagram Destroyed, 3 Mudraptors, 1 Crawler\n\nAn ideal summon for newbie cultists of underarmed ships. The low risks, easily obtainable item, and pushover success enemies make for a reliable source of basic resources.">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq coldcavern" />
      </StatusEffect>
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nRITUAL: CALYX OUTBREAK\n---\nSummoning Item: Husk Stinger\nSummons Per Item: 3\nTime Required: 60 seconds\nSuccessful Outcome: 1 Calyxanide, 1 Husk Eggs, 2 Husk\nChance of Failure: 15%\nFailure Outcome: Pentagram Destroyed, 1 Husked Crawler, 2 Husk, 1 Husk Eggs\n\nFew enemies summoned ensures that smaller crews will be less overwhelmed, but being caught off guard by a failure may easily result in a husk outbreak among the crew. Stay vigilant with this one, and you will find yourself with plenty of calyxanide.">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq husk" />
      </StatusEffect>
      <StatusEffect target="This" type="Always" setvalue="true" delay="0.1" stackable="false" msg0="---\nRITUAL: GLOWPOCALYPSE\n---\nSummoning Item: Glow/Synth/Frost Crystal\nSummons Per Item: 3\nTime Required: 40 seconds\nSuccessful Outcome: 2 Uranium, 1 Thorium, 1 Glowraptor\nChance of Failure: 30%\nFailure Outcome: Pentagram Destroyed, Small Nuclear Explosion, 3 Glowraptors\n\nA somewhat risky gamble with an alluring payoff of lots of fuel for the reactor. Recommended that your crew have the firepower to back up this venture.">
        <Conditional OriginalOutpost="eq glow" />
      </StatusEffect>
